  "description": "A ***warrant*** is the reasoning that connects [evidence](./evidence.md) to a [claim](./claim.md) — the logical bridge that explains *why* the evidence supports the claim. Stephen Toulmin introduced the term in *The Uses of Argument* (1958) to name the often-unstated assumption that makes an [argument](./argument.md) work.",
